══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
GOOGLE WORKSPACE / DRIVE (cloud files and folders)
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

DRIVE/GOOGLE-DRIVE/CLOUD-FILES/CLOUD-DOCUMENTS
  → find_files_google_workspace (search), read_files_google_workspace (download),
    write_files_google_workspace (upload), delete_files_google_workspace (delete),
    create_dirs_google_workspace (folder), share_files_google_workspace (share).
  MUST NOT: confuse with find_files/read_files (local filesystem on .33).
  NB (ADR 0128): sharing a file with a user = share_files_google_workspace
  (outbound CONSENT, ACL grant), NOT send_messages (mail) and NOT set_*
  (internal-state upsert). The recipient gets a permission, not a copy.
